2.00	Three_Mile_Island_incident	Three Mile Island accident	The Three Mile Island accident was a partial nuclear meltdown which occurred at the Three Mile Island power plant in Dauphin County, Pennsylvania, United States on March 28, 1979. It was the worst accident in U.S. commercial nuclear power plant history, and resulted in the release of small amounts of radioactive gases and radioactive iodine into the environment.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/23/Carter_TMI-2.jpg/220px-Carter_TMI-2.jpg
